con:testCase.name: UpdateInsurancePolicyPaymentFrequencyAsBulk_PositiveTC
con:testCase.con:description:
This postive test cases are targeted at the executation of change payment frequency for two policies.
First, create two policies and transfer the policy numbers.
Second, in the update step, change the payment frequency of the first contract the the first policy, e.g., from annual to monthly. change the payment frequency of the second contract the the first policy, e.g., from annual to biweekly.
Third, execute the step of 'read policy' in order to get the response.
Forth, execute the read policy to check whether the payment frequency of specific contracts have been changed.

con:testCase.name: UpdateInsurancePolicyPaymentFrequencyAsBulk_NegativeTC
con:testCase.con:description:
This negative test cases are targeted at the executation of change payment frequency for two policies.
First, re-use the two policies created in the positive test cases
Second, in the update step, change the payment frequency of the first contract the the first policy, but provide an invalid frequency code, e.g., '13'.
Third, change the payment frequency of the second contract the the first policy, e.g., from biweekly to weekly, but provide a wrong FrequencyBeginDate.
Forth, execute the read policy to check whether the payment frequency of specific contracts have not been changed.
